{
  "$comment": "Neutral shipped <fcntl.h> (POSIX) — c14d POSIX/SQLite, the first VARIADIC-extern consumer (c14c). `open`/`fcntl` are variadic (`open(path, flags, ...)` — SQLite calls both 2-arg and 3-arg; `fcntl(fd, cmd, ...)` passes &flock as a vararg, so struct flock is NOT in the signature). O_* open-flags + F_* fcntl-commands + F_RDLCK/WRLCK/UNLCK lock-types + FD_CLOEXEC (Linux octal values; arch-invariant within linux). `struct flock` is a FLAT struct (short l_type/l_whence + off_t l_start/l_len + pid_t l_pid → the layout engine derives the alignment padding to 32 bytes; x86-64-linux and arm64-linux agree, so no per-target variant). Gated availableObjectFormats:[elf] (the WSL run target). The O_*/F_* VALUES are interop-critical (a wrong flag mis-opens/mis-locks) — verified against the Linux asm-generic/fcntl.h + bits/fcntl-linux.h (64-bit: O_LARGEFILE is a 0 no-op; F_GETLK/SETLK are the native 5/6/7).",
